para.programlisting:
/**
  * @my.awesome.annotation(
  *   foo=" b a r ", 
  *   bar=3.1
  *   baz=["lorem", "ipsum"]
  * )
  */
  function foo() {
      // code
  }

section.para:
The Pia API can be used to retrieve Annotations on the fly at runtime. In order to retrieve the phpdoc which contains the Annotations it is necessary to use the reflection API. use pia\Registry;

$reflect = new \ReflectionClass('MyAnnotatedClass');
$annotations = Registry::getAnnotations($reflect);Because this  is slow it is not recommended to use it if performance matters (note that the annotations will be cached in memory by the registry therefore repeating the call won't reparse the phpdoc comment).

para.programlisting:
/**
 * @foobar(foo="bar", bar="baz")
 */
class Foo {
    /**
     * @another.annotation
     */
    private $bar;

    /**
     * @and.another.one
     */ 
    function baz() {
        // code
    }
}
